Topic: The impact of social media on mental health among university students.

Brief Rationale:
The fast development of social media has greatly altered the way students learn in a university, the way they interact and themselves.
Although these platforms are providing a source of connection and exchange of information, mental health issues like anxiety, 
depression, poor self-esteem, and sleeping disorders are also becoming associated with these platforms. The students in 
universities are especially susceptible to the pressure of studying, social expectations, and life transition.It is worth exploring how
social media affects their mental wellbeing in order to understand what the effects of it are, and how to make the social media a healthier 
resource, , help students to feel well, and influence organizational policies. 

